HEADWORD: Waxberry
<hw>Wax"ber`ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>The wax-covered fruit of the wax myrtle, or bayberry. See
<er>Bayberry</er>, and <er>Candleberry tree</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
